Textbook pricing has become a hot-button issue in academe. Allegations are rife that textbook prices are increasing faster than tuition, and that some students spend even more on textbooks than on tuition. The matter is complicated by rapidly changing technology and the expectations that print textbooks may soon be obsolete. This panel brings together two textbook editors from major publishers and two authors with extensive experience in new media to discuss why textbooks are so expensive and how the market is likely to change in the foreseeable future.